Class SavingsAccount

  • java.lang.Object
    • BankAccount
      • SavingsAccount

  • public class SavingsAccount
extends BankAccount
    The purpose of this Class is to create, hold, display, output to file, and update the specific parameters of a Savings Account. It is a sub-class of BankAccount abstract class.
    Since:
    JDK 1.8
    Version:
    1.3
    Author:
    Patrick Czermak

      • SavingsAccount

        public SavingsAccount()

      • SavingsAccount

        public SavingsAccount(java.lang.Long accountNumber,
                      double balance,
                      double interestRate,
                      double minimumBalance,
                      Client accHolder)
        Parameterized constructor to define the specific parameters a Savings Account must have for a bank account.
        Parameters:
        accountNumber - is a Long value to hold the account number which will be between 1-8 digits in length.
        balance - is a double value to hold the balance which must be a positive number.
        interestRate - is a double value randomly assigned.
        minimumBalance - is a double value which must be a positive number, and smaller than the account balance.
        accHolder - has predefined parameters in Client Class.
